  "signature": "ed25519:b7d3e9f2a1c5e8d4b6f3a9c2e7d1b5f4a8c3e6d2b9f5a1c4e7d3b8f2a6c1e9d5",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-sqa-acceptance",
      "rationale": "CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023R1) operates under ISO 9001:2015-certified QMS. Full V&V test suite executed and passed. Code is FDA-recognized per 21 CFR Part 820. Regression suite of 847 test cases executed with zero failures. Change-control log reviewed and current. Independent code audit completed by third-party assessor. All SQA artifacts archived in controlled document management system with complete audit trail."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-ncv-acceptance",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to all governing equations including turbulence closure. Observed order of accuracy (p=1.94) matches theoretical second-order scheme within 3%. Benchmark problems from ASME V&V 20-2009 suite completed with errors below 0.1% for all relevant flow regimes. Code-to-code comparison against OpenFOAM 9 confirms consistency within numerical precision. Results documented in formal verification report VR-2025-NCV-007."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-disc-acceptance",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study using three grids (coarse: 2.1M, medium: 8.4M, fine: 33.6M cells) following ASME V&V 20 GCI methodology. Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index QoI: GCI_fine = 0.87%, GCI_medium = 3.4%. Richardson extrapolation applied; asymptotic range confirmed (GCI ratio = 1.02). Temporal discretization verified separately with three time-step sizes; Courant number maintained below 0.8. All discretization error estimates archived in report DE-2025-007."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-testcond-acceptance",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions replicated in simulation with full traceability. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, 36% v/v) viscosity and density measured at 37°C ± 0.1°C. Pump rotational speed controlled to ±0.5 RPM. Flow rates measured via calibrated Coriolis flowmeter (±0.2% FS). Inlet/outlet pressure transducers calibrated to NIST traceable standards. All 5 operating points (2.5 L/min at 2500 RPM through 6.5 L/min at 3500 RPM) replicated. Test protocol documented in TP-2025-007 with IRB-equivalent oversight."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-outcomp-acceptance",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison metrics computed per ASME V&V 20-2009 for all four validation QoIs. Validation metric U_val < E for hemolysis index at all 5 operating points (maximum |E|/U_val = 0.73). Pressure-head curve: mean absolute error 2.1% across operating range. Velocity field: normalized RMS error 4.3% against LDA measurements at 12 cross-sections. Wall shear stress: 94% of measurement locations within ±2 standard deviations of experimental uncertainty band. Systematic bias analysis performed; no statistically significant bias detected (p>0.05)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-qoi-acceptance",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) directly maps to clinical hemolysis risk metric used in FDA guidance. Secondary QoIs (exposure time, scalar shear stress) are mechanistically linked to NIH through validated power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger). QoI traceability matrix documents linkage from simulation output to clinical decision criterion (RH < 1). Sensitivity analysis confirms NIH is the dominant QoI; secondary QoIs contribute <8% to total decision uncertainty. QoI relevance formally reviewed by clinical subject-matter expert (documented in SME-review-2025-007)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-valrel-acceptance",
      "rationale": "Validation hierarchy constructed per ASME V&V 10-2019 with four tiers: unit, benchmark, subsystem, and system-level. System-level validation performed on the identical FDA generic pump geometry under CPB-representative conditions. All 5 COU operating points covered by validation experiments. Fluid properties, geometry, boundary conditions, and rotational speed match COU within stated uncertainty bounds. Validation-to-COU applicability matrix completed; no unvalidated extrapolation identified. Validation relevance score: 0.94 on [0,1] scale per internal rubric."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-nse-acceptance",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via residual norms and QoI stabilization. All simulations converged to residual norms below 1e-6 for continuity and momentum; hemolysis index QoI variation < 0.01% over final 500 iterations. Round-off error estimated via double-precision arithmetic analysis: negligible relative to discretization error (ratio < 0.001). Linear solver tolerance set to 1e-10; preconditioned GMRES with ILU(2) factorization. Solver error budget formally quantified and included in total uncertainty estimate."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-useerr-acceptance",
      "rationale": "Independent simulation replication performed by second analyst using identical inputs; QoI agreement within 0.3%. Simulation setup checklist (42 items) completed and signed by primary and reviewing analysts. Boundary condition specification reviewed against experimental protocol by third party. Automated input validation scripts detect out-of-range parameters prior to solver execution. All simulation setup files version-controlled in Git repository with SHA-256 checksums. User error risk formally assessed as negligible after procedural controls applied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-modelform-acceptance",
      "rationale": "RANS k-omega SST turbulence model selected based on systematic model-form comparison study (k-epsilon, k-omega SST, RSM, LES-Smagorinsky) against experimental data. SST model achieved lowest validation metric (U_val) for hemolysis index QoI across all operating points. Model-form uncertainty quantified using Bayesian model averaging over four turbulence closure candidates; 95% credible interval width = 4.2% of mean NIH. Hemolysis power-law model parameters calibrated to 23 independent experimental datasets; calibration uncertainty propagated to QoI. Model-form error formally bounded and included in total uncertainty budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-modelinputs-acceptance",
      "rationale": "All 34 model input parameters characterized with probability distributions derived from experimental measurements or literature meta-analysis. Input uncertainty propagated via quasi-Monte Carlo sampling (Sobol sequence, N=4096). Total-order Sobol sensitivity indices computed for all inputs; top 5 inputs account for 91% of output variance. Blood analog viscosity and pump rotational speed identified as dominant inputs (S_T = 0.43 and 0.31 respectively). Input correlation structure captured via Gaussian copula. Full input uncertainty characterization documented in UQ report UQ-2025-007 linked to this assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-testsamples-acceptance",
      "rationale": "Experimental dataset comprises N=15 independent pump specimens manufactured to identical specifications with full dimensional inspection. Three replicate experiments per operating point per specimen (N_total = 225 data points). Statistical power analysis confirms 90% power to detect 5% difference in NIH at alpha=0.05. Specimen-to-specimen variability characterized and included in experimental uncertainty budget. Sample representativeness confirmed via dimensional metrology: all critical dimensions within ±0.5% of nominal. Batch-to-batch material variability assessed via viscometry; CV < 1.2% across all batches."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-eqvinputs-acceptance",
      "rationale": "Formal equivalency assessment performed for all boundary conditions between validation experiments and COU simulations. Reynolds number matching confirmed at all 5 operating points (Re_sim / Re_exp ratio: 0.997–1.003). Womersley number equivalency verified for pulsatile flow components. Inlet velocity profiles extracted from experimental PIV measurements and imposed as simulation boundary conditions. Geometric equivalency confirmed via CT scan comparison of test specimens against CAD nominal: maximum deviation 0.08 mm. Equivalency gaps identified (blood vs. glycerol-water analog) formally quantified and bounded via rheological sensitivity analysis; impact on NIH < 2.1%."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-mrl5-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed at requiredLevel 5 and achievedLevel 5, consistent with Model Risk Level 5 requirements for a Class II device with High decision consequence. The total uncertainty budget for the primary QoI (NIH) has been formally quantified via quasi-Monte Carlo UQ (N=4096): 95% prediction interval width is 8.7% of mean NIH, well within the 15% acceptance threshold established in the credibility plan. Validation metric U_val < E at all 5 operating points confirms model predictive capability within the COU. Sensitivity analysis identifies viscosity and rotational speed as dominant uncertainty drivers; both are tightly controlled in the COU deployment context. Model-form uncertainty is formally bounded via Bayesian model averaging. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 criterion is met with 97.3% probability under the full input uncertainty distribution, satisfying the pre-specified 95% confidence threshold. Independent replication, third-party code audit, and complete provenance chain from raw experimental data through to decision output have been verified. No unresolved credibility gaps, open findings, or weakeners are present. The assessment team unanimously accepts the simulation results as credible for the stated COU.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
